snippet.title: Will Smith Reveals Why He Wanted To K*ll His Dad
snippet.description:
Will Smith Reveals Why He Wanted To K*ll His Dad

Just like his character from Fresh Prince, Will had a very complicated relationship with his father William Carroll Smith. 

And complicated is probably an understatement.

While Will’s father never abandoned him or neglected him, he did something so horrifying that at one point during his childhood, Will actually contemplated killing his father.

Will Smith was born on September 25th, 1968, in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, to Caroline, a Philadelphia school board administrator, and Willard Carroll Smith Sr., a U.S. Air Force veteran, and refrigeration engineer. 

In his new tell-all memoir Will, Will explains that he had such a hard time dealing with his mother’s departure that he even contemplated suicide at one point.
